={
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct",
  "response_format": { "type": "json_object" },
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "You are a grocery receipt reader for Bahrain bills. Read EVERY page of the receipt image(s) and return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown, no extra words) in EXACTLY this shape: {\"store_name\": string|null, \"bill_date\": \"YYYY-MM-DD\"|null, \"line_items\": [{\"item_name\": string, \"category\": string, \"quantity\": number, \"unit_price\": number, \"discount\": number, \"line_total\": number, \"vat_rate\": number, \"vat_amount\": number, \"is_essential\": boolean}], \"subtotal\": number|null, \"vat_total\": number|null, \"grand_total\": number|null}. RULES: (1) item_name = the English product description. (2) quantity = the Qty column (use 1 if missing). (3) unit_price = the Price column. (4) discount = the Disc. column (use 0 if none). (5) line_total = the value in the RIGHTMOST 'Total' column for that line. This is the amount actually paid (after discount, including VAT) and is the LARGEST money value on the line. NEVER take line_total from the 'Net' or 'Vat' columns. (6) vat_rate = READ the printed VAT % column for that line (0 or 10). Do NOT guess it. (7) vat_amount = the printed Vat amount for that line. (8) is_essential = true only when vat_rate is 0. (9) category MUST be one of: Fruits & Vegetables, Dairy, Bakery, Meat & Seafood, Grains & Pulses, Pantry & Cooking, Snacks, Beverages, Household, Personal Care, Other. (10) Skip non-product lines like totals, change, loyalty points and card details. (11) All money values are numbers only."
        },
        {
          "type": "image_url",
          "image_url": { "url": "data:{{ $json.body.mime_type }};base64,{{ $json.body.image_base64 }}" }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
const billId = $input.first().json.id;       // the new bill's id
const parsed = $('Parse').first().json;       // the items from earlier

return parsed.line_items.map(it => ({
  json: {
    bill_id: billId,
    item_name: it.item_name || null,
    category: it.category || 'Other',
    quantity: it.quantity ?? 1,
    unit_price: it.unit_price ?? null,
    discount: it.discount ?? 0,
    line_total: it.line_total ?? null,
    vat_rate: it.vat_rate ?? null,
    vat_amount: it.vat_amount ?? null,
    is_essential: Number(it.vat_rate) === 0
  }
}));

const groq = $input.first().json;
const data = JSON.parse(groq.choices[0].message.content);

const items = data.line_items || [];
const byCategory = {};
let essentials = 0, taxed = 0, itemsSum = 0;

for (const it of items) {
  const cat = it.category || 'Other';
  const total = Number(it.line_total || 0);
  itemsSum += total;
  byCategory[cat] = (byCategory[cat] || 0) + total;
  if (Number(it.vat_rate) === 0) essentials += total;  // 0% VAT = staple
  else taxed += total;                                  // 10% VAT
}

// Safety net: do the item totals match the printed grand total?
const grand = Number(data.grand_total || itemsSum);
const needsReview = Math.abs(itemsSum - grand) > 0.05;

const billDate = data.bill_date || new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);

return [{
  json: {
    user_name: $('Webhook').first().json.body.user_name,
    store_name: data.store_name || null,
    bill_date: data.bill_date || null,
    bill_month: billDate.slice(0, 7),
    subtotal: data.subtotal ?? null,
    vat_total: data.vat_total ?? null,
    grand_total: data.grand_total ?? null,
    essentials_total: Number(essentials.toFixed(3)),
    taxed_total: Number(taxed.toFixed(3)),
    needs_review: needsReview,
    category_subtotals: byCategory,  // for the UI
    line_items: items                // for the next save step
  }
}];
